    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework demonstrates sufficient credibility for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU. Eleven of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. Test conditions factor achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the conservative nature of the single test condition relative to clinical loading. Quantitative output comparison confirms all three QoIs within acceptance bounds (E/uval <1.96, percent difference <10%). The package is accepted for regulatory submission.",
